<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="502" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d502">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/829a.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Smith</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-09">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 9, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>All reports from Haiti indicate that Zamor Government will probably be
                            stable and able to preserve order, but the President prefers to delay
                            recognition until situation is more settled.</p>
                        <p>Please inquire of Government what guaranties it can give as to its
                            permanence and ability to protect lives and property of foreigners. Also
                            report how many provinces have accepted the new President and how many
                            are in revolt.</p>
                        <p>What is the attitude of Davilmar Theodore and what prospect is there of
                            his being able to disturb the new Government?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>